    "updated_at": "2017-04-11T02:57:35Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It seems like the real issue is that the ToolTip is obscuring other targeted actors.\r\n\r\n1) Modifying the rendering of a ToolTip should be based on whether the ToolTip obscures other targeted actors or just modify when multiple actors are targeted to simplify the check.\r\n\r\n2) The ToolTip can be modified instead of being completely disabled. The whole ToolTip can be made more transparent.\r\n\r\n3) The simplest solution might be to add a hotkey to toggle the ToolTip (perhaps temporarily) and let the user decide ToolTip rendering.\r\n\r\n4) Another option is to make the ToolTip disappear/appear after a timeout. Mouse movement would cause it to reappear/disappear.\r\n\r\nAll of these invalidate #13064 as a solution."
  },
